# Plinth per-project config. Never overwritten by plinth update.
# Agent-immutable (protected-paths). Four knobs, all set-once:
# spec_path: canonical spec — file (SPEC.md) or directory tree (spec/).
# exec_gated: space-separated grep -E patterns for execution-gated paths;
#   RUNTIME: review findings there route to the run gate instead of blocking.
# smoke_cmd: the real-run command the Smoke workflow executes on the
#   self-hosted runner (empty = smoke job no-ops green).
# tier2_extra: grep -E pattern; changed paths matching it are forced to Tier 2
#   (highest-consequence review). Additive only — raises a file's tier, never
#   lowers it. Invalid regex fails closed (whole change → Tier 2). Here it lifts
#   this repo's own product source (shared/, templates/, bin/) out of the generic
#   "docs are inert" default, since those .md/.sh files ARE Plinth.
# Everything else has working defaults.
spec_path = MANUAL.md
tier2_extra = (^|/)(shared|templates|bin)/
